Definition: a progressive form of presenile dementia that is similar to senile dementia except that it usually starts in the 40s or 50s
Example: first symptoms are impaired memory which is followed by impaired thought and speech and finally complete helplessness
Synonyms: s_disease, s, Alzheimers, presenile_dementia, a, progressive, form, of, presenile, dementia, that, is, similar, to, senile, except, it, usually, starts, in, the, or, first, symptoms, are, impaired, memory, which, followed, by, thought, and, speech, finally, complete, helplessness
Category: noun.state
